# Secret-loading pattern for this repo.
#
# Real values live in 1Password (preferred) or a local .env that is
# gitignored. Code must read via env vars at runtime (os.environ[...]),
# never embedding literal tokens.
#
# Example via 1Password CLI (op) wrapper:
#   export API_TOKEN="$(mypw.py --vault <vault> --item <item> --field token)"
# Or via dotenv:
#   cp .env.example .env  && edit .env to add real values  (NEVER commit .env)
#
# List the variables your code reads below — names only, no values.

API_TOKEN=
API_URL=

# --- External dependency overrides (optional) ---
# Canonical declarations live in _tooling/external_deps.py (EXTERNAL_DEPS); these vars only
# OVERRIDE a path when a dependency isn't on $PATH or at its conventional sibling.
# Most users need none of these. See ~/obsidian/42-Git/README_INTERDEPENDENCIES.md.
# BROWSER_PY_BIN=/abs/path/to/browser.py   # an executable / script
# <DEP>_ROOT=/abs/path/to/some-repo        # a repo root directory
# <DEP>_PATH=/abs/path/to/some/file        # a specific file / data path
